      "This guide covers everything Colorado homeowners need to know heading into the 2026 hail season. When the storms come, which areas are most at risk, how to prepare your roof and your insurance policy, and exactly what to do when hail hits your neighborhood.",

      "When Is Hail Season in Colorado?",
      "Colorado's hail season officially spans April through September, but the window of real risk is narrower than that. The peak months are May, June, July, and August. June is historically the worst month, with more large-hail events than any other month in the state. Late afternoon and early evening are the prime hours. That classic Colorado pattern of clear mornings building to afternoon thunderstorms is the engine behind most hail events.",
