      "What makes Colorado particularly vulnerable is geography. The Front Range sits at the collision point between warm, moist air flowing north from the Gulf of Mexico and cold, dry air dropping south from Canada. The Rocky Mountains add lift to the equation, forcing air upward and supercharging thunderstorm development. The result is one of the most hail-prone regions on the planet.",

